{"_id":"PaZmYojg0yLdXbj2","name":"Bless*","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the caster and his or her allies (within a 50' radius of the caster) a bonus of +1 on attack rolls, morale checks (for monsters or NPCs allied with the caster), and saving throws against magical <strong>fear</strong>.</p>\n<p>The reverse of <strong>bless</strong> is called <strong>bane</strong>. It fills the caster's enemies (within a 50' radius) with fear and doubt, causing each affected creature to suffer a &ndash;1 penalty on attack rolls, morale checks, and saving throws against magical <strong>fear</strong>.</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"1 minute/level","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"50' radius","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"phLtD0yIJ7OVPera","name":"Charm Animal","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to charm one or more animals, in much the same fashion as <strong>charm person</strong>, at a rate of 1 hit die per caster level. The caster may decide which individual animals out of a mixed group are to be affected first; excess hit dice of effect are ignored. No saving throw is allowed, either for normal or giant-sized animals, but creatures of more fantastic nature (as determined by the GM) are allowed a save vs. Spells to resist. When the duration expires, the animals will resume normal activity immediately.</p>\n<p>This spell does not grant the caster any special means of communication with the affected animals; if combined with <strong>speak with animals</strong>, this spell becomes significantly more useful.</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"level+1d4 rounds","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"60'","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"tS0Qcnk4AKGrfCW5","name":"Find Traps","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>This spell permits the caster to detect a variety of traps, both mechanical and magical. When the caster moves within 30&rsquo; of a trap, he or she will see it glow with a faint greenish-blue aura. The caster is not, however, able to detect certain natural hazards such as quicksand, a sinkhole, or unsafe walls of natural rock. The spell also does not bestow the caster with the knowledge needed to disarm the trap, nor any details about its type or nature.</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"3 turns","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"30'","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"PxkViYJkIAm2Rxj8","name":"Hold Person","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>This spell will render any living (not undead) human, demi-human or humanoid creature paralyzed. Creatures larger than ogres will not be affected by this spell. Targets of the spell are aware, and breathe normally, but cannot take any actions, including speech. A successful save vs. Spells will negate the effect. The spell may be cast at a single person, who makes his or her save at -2, or at a group, in which case 1d4 of the creatures in the group may be affected.</p>\n<p>A winged creature which is paralyzed cannot flap its wings and falls (if in flight at the time). A paralyzed swimmer can&rsquo;t swim and may drown.</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"2d8 turns","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"180'","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"iVOrXqxThotLC7se","name":"Resist Fire","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>This abjuration grants a creature temporary immunity to fire and heat. Minor heat or fire (such as exposure to normal flames) is ignored by the affected creature. Against more significant heat or fire (such as a <strong>fireball</strong>), the affected creature gains a bonus of +3 on saving throws, and all damage from such attacks is reduced by half (round up).</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"1 round/level","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"touch","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"brrIcBx4yXAd8eZF","name":"Silence 15' Radius","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Upon the casting of this spell, complete silence prevails within a 15' radius around the target. All sound is stopped: Conversation is impossible, spells cannot be cast, and no noise whatsoever issues from, enters, or passes through the area. The spell can be cast on a point in space, making the effect stationary, or it may be cast on a mobile object. The spell can be centered on a creature, and the effect then radiates from the creature and moves as it moves. An unwilling creature receives a save vs. Spells to negate the spell. If an item in another creature&rsquo;s possession is targeted, that creature also receives a save vs. Spells to negate. This spell provides a defense against sonic or language-based attacks or spells.</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"2 rounds/level","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"360'","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"UI2fdqBr7pXnCJdA","name":"Speak with Animals","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>The caster can comprehend and communicate with any one animal (normal or giant sized, but not magical or monstrous) that is in sight of the caster and able to hear him or her. The caster may change which animal he or she is speaking with at will, once per round. The spell doesn&rsquo;t alter the animal&rsquo;s reaction or attitude towards the caster; a standard reaction roll should be made to determine this. Furthermore, more intelligent animals are likely to be terse and evasive, while less intelligent ones make inane comments. However, if an animal is friendly toward the caster, it may be willing to grant some favor or service.</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"1 turn/4 levels","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"special","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"F7soTGqOyBm9crUj","name":"Spiritual Hammer","type":"spell","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-white.webp","data":{"description":"<p>This spell causes a warhammer made of pure force to spring into existence, attacking any foe chosen by the Cleric within range once per round. It deals 1d6 hit points of damage per strike, +1 point per three caster levels (maximum of +5). It uses the caster&rsquo;s normal attack bonus, striking as a magical weapon, and thus can inflict damage upon creatures that are only hit by magic weapons. If the hammer goes beyond the spell range, the Cleric loses sight of it, or the caster ceases to direct it, the hammer disappears. The hammer cannot be attacked or harmed by physical attacks, but <strong>dispel magic</strong>, <strong>disintegrate</strong>, or a <strong>rod of cancellation</strong> will dispel it.</p>","class":{"value":"Cleric","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Class"},"duration":{"value":"1 round/level","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Duration"},"prepared":{"value":0,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Prepared"},"range":{"value":"30'","label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.Range"},"spellLevel":{"value":2,"label":"BASICFANTASYRPG.SpellLevel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ibGMZPma8kUz3MmY":3},"flags":{}}
